# Useful MySQL Commands

## Show databases

```sql
SHOW DATABASES;
```

## Use database

```sql
USE userdb;
```

## Show tables

```sql
SHOW TABLES;
```

## Describe table

```sql
DESC table_name;
```

## View all records

```sql
SELECT * FROM table_name;
```

## Count records

```sql
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM table_name;
```

## Create database

```sql
CREATE DATABASE database_name;
```

## Drop database

```sql
DROP DATABASE database_name;
```

## Create table

```sql
CREATE TABLE employee(
id INT PRIMARY KEY,
name VARCHAR(100)
);
```

## Insert data

```sql
INSERT INTO employee VALUES(1,'Megha');
```

## Update data

```sql
UPDATE employee
SET name='John'
WHERE id=1;
```

## Delete data

```sql
DELETE FROM employee
WHERE id=1;
```

## Drop table

```sql
DROP TABLE employee;
```

## Exit MySQL

```sql
EXIT;
```

